Johannesburg – Registration at the University of Limpopo (UL) for the 2022 Academic Year for first-entering students is still open and will continue until 04 February. Most vacancies for qualifying first-entering students are in the School of Accountancy and in the Faculty of Science and Agriculture. Lectures for first entering students will therefore only commence on Monday, 07 February 2022. It is important to note that registration is strictly online to manage the risk of the Covid-19 pandemic and to comply with the safety protocols in terms of the National Disaster Management Act. Details are available on the University website, www.ul.ac.za. Regarding those students in need of financial assistance, the University is in constant engagement with the National Student Financial Aid System (NSFAS) for confirmations to facilitate the registration of qualifying first-entering students. All other queries in connection with registration can be directed to our call centre. The number is +2715 268 3332. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.